---
title: Neural Oscillator Phase States
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    state CognitivePhases {
        direction LR
        THETA: 4-12 Hz (encoding, exploration)
        GAMMA: 30-100 Hz (local computation)
        ALPHA: 8-12 Hz (idling, inhibition)
        DELTA: 0.5-4 Hz (deep sleep, SWR)

        THETA --> GAMMA: Focus engagement
        GAMMA --> THETA: Broaden attention
        THETA --> ALPHA: Disengage idle
        ALPHA --> THETA: Re-engage input
        ALPHA --> DELTA: Sleep onset
        DELTA --> ALPHA: Lightening
    }

    state SleepOscillations {
        direction LR
        WA: Awake alpha
        SS: Sleep spindles (N2)
        SW: Slow waves (N3)
        RT: REM theta

        WA --> SS: Sleep onset
        SS --> SW: Deepening
        SW --> RT: REM entry
        RT --> SS: New cycle
        SS --> WA: Wake
    }

    TGC: Theta-Gamma Coupling (memory encoding)

    CognitivePhases --> TGC: Active encoding
    TGC --> CognitivePhases: Retrieval mode
